-- Kan Says Japan Will Try to Avoid Bond Sales for Extra Budget, Kyodo Says
-- B y   G o   O n o m i t s u
-- 2010-09-24T01:12:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-24/kan-says-japan-will-try-to-avoid-bond-sales-for-extra-budget-kyodo-says.html
Japanese Prime Minister Naoto Kan
said he will seek to avoid selling government bonds to fund a
supplementary budget for the current fiscal year, Kyodo News
reported. He was speaking to reporters in New York, Kyodo said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Go Onomitsu in Tokyo at 
